Diamed Diagnostic Center is a 3 storey fully equipped diagnostic center that is being developed along T.F. Kuboye Road in Lekki Phase 1 near Oniru Market. Also Read: La Definition Development in Victoria Island, Lagos, Nigeria Upon completion, the center will increase the availability of a range of clinical services including radiology, pathology, endoscopy, and cardiac services and dialysis, to aid a more accurate diagnosis of patients and serve as a diagnostics hub for hospitals and medical professionals.  According to the project manager, Utopian Consulting LLC (UC), which is an international healthcare company whose focus is to provide comprehensive, world-class solutions to the needs of international healthcare providers, this should mean cheaper access to high-performing diagnostic equipment, managed by dedicated medical professionals. In addition to Utopian as project manager, Diamed Diagnostic Center project has Arbico Plc, a full-service building and civil engineering construction company as the main contractor, Geyser Hahn Architects, a specialist healthcare practice established by Liezel Geyser-Hahn and Alexander Hahn as the architect, and Morgan Omonitan & Abe Ltd (MO&A), an engineering & development consulting firm as the structural engineer.